  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "TECHNICIAN",
  "description": "<p>Diagnose,\ntroubleshoot and repair mobile devices;</p><p>•    Quality control and testing of repaired\ndevices to ensure full functionality. Resolve/manage customer inquiries;</p><p>•    Able to interact positively with customers\nat the storefront and over the phone;</p><p>•    Ability to multi-task between repairs and\ncustomer service;</p><p>•    Other related duties as required;</p><p>•    Maintain and use repair tools and equipment.\nIncluding software and in-store POS system to track repair tickets and\ninventory;</p><p>•    Strategically plan the order of operations\nto ensure a successful repair;</p><p>•    Provide estimates and quotes;</p><p>•    Glass only replacement on Samsung and iPads;</p><p>•    Microscopic Board work; component\nreplacement Hand-solder SMT components,</p><p>•    remove and replace thru-hole comp without\nboard damage,</p><p>•    solder wires and cables,</p><p>•    Diagnosis, troubleshoot and repair mobile\ndevices;</p><p>•    identify assembly and documents issues;</p><p>•    Repair logic board issues from water damage.</p><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><p>•    Excellent knowledge of customer service best\npractice with previous experience;</p><p>•    Ability to repair a variety of mobile\ndevices (i.e., iPhone, Samsung, LG, Motorola, Sony, Huawei and OnePlus phone,\nand iPads.);</p><p>•    Ability to communicate effectively with a\nwide variety of people in a professional manner, face to face, on the telephone\nand in writing;</p><p>•    Knowledge of mobile devices including\nmanufacturers, operating systems, and network service providers;</p><p>•    Willing to work flexibly and with\nenthusiasm;</p><p>•    Excellent organizational skills;</p><p>•    Good attention to detail and ability to show\ninitiative;</p><p>•    Ability to demonstrate practical\ntroubleshooting and problem analysis techniques;</p><p>•    Ability to plan and prioritize your workload\nwithout supervision;</p>",
